Solar panels require mining for materials, which can be environmentally damaging. Wind turbines can affect bird and bat populations. Hydro can disrupt ecosystems and displace communities. So, the environmental impact isn't zero for renewables, but generally lower than fossil fuels.

Practical aspects. Reliability and consistency. Solar depends on sunlight, so it's not available at night or during cloudy days. Wind depends on wind conditions. Also, the infrastructure for renewables might be less developed in some areas, requiring more investment in grid upgrades.
